To take and send the photograph.

00:13:11.980 --> 00:13:15.100
Now the Hebrew on the stones,

00:13:15.100 --> 00:13:18.680
sometimes can give you some
interesting information.

00:13:18.680 --> 00:13:23.520
The Hebrew on these stones
includes the names of the deceased

00:13:23.520 --> 00:13:25.710
and their father's
names, typical things

00:13:25.710 --> 00:13:28.740
to find on a Jewish tombstone.

00:13:28.740 --> 00:13:32.990
This also includes their
death dates, the English,

00:13:32.990 --> 00:13:38.500
the Arabic numeral that you
see on the gravestones are only

00:13:38.500 --> 00:13:40.850
of the year of their deaths.

00:13:40.850 --> 00:13:45.830
But the Hebrew gives us the
date of their deaths too.

00:13:45.830 --> 00:13:52.560 position:56%
Now, sometimes the Hebrew dates are
off by a day from the English dates,

00:13:52.560 --> 00:13:55.190
